\section{What the Data Shows}

These are not obscure titles gathering dust. The {{ stats.booksFound }} books found in this survey account for {{ total_copies | format_number }} copies actively cataloged across the state. Many are children's picture books, middle-grade novels, and young-adult fiction---genres aimed squarely at minors. \emph{Gender Queer}, a graphic memoir depicting oral sex between minors, appears in 24 systems. \emph{Sex is a funny word}, a sex-education book targeting children as young as seven, appears in 24 systems. \emph{It feels good to be yourself}, a picture book pushing gender-identity ideology on preschoolers, appears in 25 systems. These are not edge cases; they are the products of a systematic effort to normalize sexually explicit and ideologically radical material in children's sections of Texas public libraries.

Each library profile in Chapter~\ref{ch:profiles} lists every harmful title that system holds, so that parents and community members can see exactly what is available at their local library and make informed decisions about how to engage with their library boards.
